general.description:
I work as a solicitor at King & Wood Mallesons (KWM) in the M&A (Corporate) team, having joined the firm's Melbourne office at the start of 2015.  I was admitted to practise as an Australian lawyer in October 2015 and completed a 6-month secondment to KWM's Hong Kong office in 2016, where I worked in the Banking & Finance team. I also spent 6 months in the Dispute Resolution (Intellectual Property) team. 

Before starting at KWM, I completed a 12 month posting as Aide to the Governor of Victoria in 2014 and returned to the University of Melbourne to complete the final semester of my law degree (Juris Doctor). Prior to that, I worked at the University for 3 years as a macro- and microeconomics tutor.  

Outside of the law, my main interests are in the fields of:
     - economics;
     - cities and infrastructure planning;
     - architecture;
     - homelessness and poverty reduction; and 
     - drug addiction and dependence.

